President Obama released a statement expressing his condolences on the passing of Leonard Nimoy, best known for his role as Spock in Star Trek. The President praised Nimoy's love for the arts and humanities, his support for the sciences, and his generosity with his talent and time. He described Spock as cool, logical, and level-headed, representing Star Trek's optimistic and inclusive vision of humanity's future. The President shared a personal memory of meeting Nimoy in 2007 and greeting him with the Vulcan salute. He concluded by expressing his sympathy to Nimoy's family, friends, and fans.